news.title: Ghaziabad development body frees ₹800 crore land for Indirapuram Extension project
news.para: A GDA official said the land parcel will be clubbed with the Indirapuram Extension scheme — covering an area of 34 hectares — where the development authority is planning a new township.

news.title: No homes on zudpi jungles will be demolished: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: Chairing a high-level meeting at Mantralaya to address the long standing issue, Bawankule warned senior officials from revenue and forest departments that delays in regularising such homes will not be tolerated.

news.title: Noida authority urges Uttar Pradesh government to review Gardenia Aims Developers' debt plan
news.para: The authority said that if allowed, the move would contradict a cabinet-approved policy for stalled projects, which requires defaulting builders to deposit 25% of dues before accessing relief measures.
